  "text": "Under the proper conditions, Cl Ϫ channel activation is another potential mechanism to explain stretch-in-duced depolarization of VSM. Chloride channels have been implicated in agonist-induced depolarization of VSM [CITATION_1] . In smooth muscle, the estimated equilibrium potential for Cl Ϫ (E Cl ) is somewhere between Ϫ47 and Ϫ10 mV (106), with the variation probably reflecting differences in the activity or expression of different Cl Ϫ transport systems in different vessels. If E Cl were more positive than the resting potential of the cell (3), opening of a Cl Ϫ -selective channel would allow Cl Ϫ efflux, producing depolarization. Possible candidates mediating this effect would be a Ca 2ϩ -activated Cl Ϫ current (156, 221) and a volume-activated Cl Ϫ current (387), both of which have been described in VSM.",
